# A dep TOP-LEVEL fn reads both a runtime-indexed data table (`table.index idx`)
# and a labeled data constant (`flag.hi`). Cross-unit, the access-base node is
# not stamped DATA and userFnId is main-relative, so emitDataIndexCall + the fold
# must re-resolve the block by name. Mirrors zlexer isidchar's charflags/charflag.
# Runs + prints the value: a fold-only or index-only fix compiles but computes wrong.
main: function is {
    v0: xunit_data_topfn.classify i: 0.u8
    v1: xunit_data_topfn.classify i: 1.u8
    v2: xunit_data_topfn.classify i: 2.u8
    print "c=\{v0},\{v1},\{v2}"
}
